# RHACM installation process
https://access.redhat.com/documentation/en-us/red_hat_advanced_cluster_management_for_kubernetes/2.4/html-single/install/index
https://access.redhat.com/documentation/en-us/red_hat_advanced_cluster_management_for_kubernetes/2.4/html-single/install/index#doc-wrapper

# OpenShift cluster details
  > One OCP cluster to be on running state with latest version
  > Available resources to deploy and configuration RHACM
  > Install RHACM operator from operator Hub or through cli
  > Configure RHACM Hub cluster
  > Add or import Managed cluster
  > Create new cluster using RHACM
  > Upgrade Hub cluster or Managed cluster using RHACM 
  
  
# Additional validation
  > Internet connectivity between Hub & managed cluster
  > oc or kubectl command line
  > base64 utility
  > cluster admin permission
  
  
  



